{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, I'd like to spend a few minutes with you folks today"},{"time":3000,"text":"imagining what our planet might look like in a thousand years."},{"time":6000,"text":"But before I do that,"},{"time":8000,"text":"I need to talk to you about synthetic materials like plastics,"},{"time":11000,"text":"which require huge amounts of energy to create"},{"time":14000,"text":"and, because of their disposal issues,"},{"time":16000,"text":"are slowly poisoning our planet."},{"time":18000,"text":"I also want to tell you and share with you"},{"time":20000,"text":"how my team and I"},{"time":22000,"text":"have been using mushrooms over the last three years."},{"time":25000,"text":"Not like that. (Laughter)"},{"time":27000,"text":"We're using mushrooms to create an entirely new class of materials,"},{"time":30000,"text":"which perform a lot like plastics during their use,"},{"time":33000,"text":"but are made from crop waste"},{"time":35000,"text":"and are totally compostable at the end of their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"(Cheering)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"But first,"},{"time":42000,"text":"I need to talk to you about what I consider one of the most egregious offenders"},{"time":45000,"text":"in the disposable plastics category."},{"time":47000,"text":"This is a material you all know is Styrofoam,"},{"time":49000,"text":"but I like to think of it as toxic white stuff."},{"time":53000,"text":"In a single cubic foot of this material --"},{"time":55000,"text":"about what would come around your computer or large television --"},{"time":57000,"text":"you have the same energy content"},{"time":59000,"text":"of about a liter and a half of petrol."},{"time":61000,"text":"Yet, after just a few weeks of use,"},{"time":63000,"text":"you'll throw this material in the trash."},{"time":66000,"text":"And this isn't just found in packaging."},{"time":68000,"text":"20 billion dollars of this material is produced every year,"},{"time":70000,"text":"in everything from building materials to surfboards"},{"time":73000,"text":"to coffee cups to table tops."},{"time":75000,"text":"And that's not the only place it's found."},{"time":78000,"text":"The EPA estimates, in the United States,"},{"time":80000,"text":"by volume, this material occupies 25 percent of our landfills."},{"time":84000,"text":"Even worse is when it finds its way into our natural environment --"},{"time":87000,"text":"on the side of the road or next to a river."},{"time":89000,"text":"If it's not picked up by a human, like me and you,"},{"time":92000,"text":"it'll stay there for thousands and thousands of years."},{"time":94000,"text":"Perhaps even worse"},{"time":96000,"text":"is when it finds its way into our oceans, like in the great plastic gyre,"},{"time":99000,"text":"where these materials are being mechanically broken"},{"time":101000,"text":"into smaller and smaller bits,"},{"time":103000,"text":"but they're not really going away."},{"time":105000,"text":"They're not biologically compatible."},{"time":107000,"text":"They're basically fouling up"},{"time":109000,"text":"Earth's respiratory and circulatory systems."},{"time":111000,"text":"And because these materials are so prolific,"},{"time":114000,"text":"because they're found in so many places,"},{"time":116000,"text":"there's one other place you'll find this material, styrene,"},{"time":119000,"text":"which is made from benzene, a known carcinogen."},{"time":121000,"text":"You'll find it inside of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"So, for all these reasons,"},{"time":126000,"text":"I think we need better materials,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and there are three key principles we can use to guide these materials."},{"time":132000,"text":"The first is feedstocks."},{"time":134000,"text":"Today, we use a single feedstock, petroleum,"},{"time":137000,"text":"to heat our homes, power our cars"},{"time":139000,"text":"and make most of the materials you see around you."},{"time":142000,"text":"We recognize this is a finite resource,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and it's simply crazy to do this, to put a liter and a half of petrol in the trash"},{"time":147000,"text":"every time you get a package."},{"time":149000,"text":"Second of all, we should really strive to use far less energy"},{"time":151000,"text":"in creating these materials."},{"time":153000,"text":"I say far less, because 10 percent isn't going to cut it."},{"time":156000,"text":"We should be talking about half, a quarter,"},{"time":158000,"text":"one-tenth the energy content."},{"time":161000,"text":"And lastly, and I think perhaps most importantly,"},{"time":164000,"text":"we should be creating materials"},{"time":166000,"text":"that fit into what I call nature's recycling system."},{"time":169000,"text":"This recycling system has been in place for the last billion years."},{"time":172000,"text":"I fit into it, you fit into it,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and a hundred years tops, my body can return to the Earth with no preprocessing."},{"time":177000,"text":"Yet that packaging I got in the mail yesterday"},{"time":179000,"text":"is going to last for thousands of years."},{"time":181000,"text":"This is crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"But nature provides us with a really good model here."},{"time":186000,"text":"When a tree's done using its leaves --"},{"time":188000,"text":"its solar collectors, these amazing molecular photon capturing devices --"},{"time":191000,"text":"at the end of a season,"},{"time":193000,"text":"it doesn't pack them up, take them to the leaf reprocessing center"},{"time":196000,"text":"and have them melted down to form new leaves."},{"time":198000,"text":"It just drops them, the shortest distance possible,"},{"time":201000,"text":"to the forest floor,"},{"time":203000,"text":"where they're actually upcycled into next year's topsoil."},{"time":205000,"text":"And this gets us back to the mushrooms."},{"time":209000,"text":"Because in nature,"},{"time":211000,"text":"mushrooms are the recycling system."},{"time":213000,"text":"And what we've discovered"},{"time":215000,"text":"is, by using a part of the mushroom you've probably never seen --"},{"time":217000,"text":"analogous to its root structure; it's called mycelium --"},{"time":220000,"text":"we can actually grow materials"},{"time":222000,"text":"with many of the same properties of conventional synthetics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"Now, mycelium is an amazing material,"},{"time":227000,"text":"because it's a self-assembling material."},{"time":229000,"text":"It actually takes things we would consider waste --"},{"time":231000,"text":"things like seed husks or woody biomass --"},{"time":234000,"text":"and can transform them into a chitinous polymer,"},{"time":236000,"text":"which you can form into almost any shape."},{"time":238000,"text":"In our process,"},{"time":240000,"text":"we basically use it as a glue."},{"time":242000,"text":"And by using mycelium as a glue,"},{"time":244000,"text":"you can mold things just like you do in the plastic industry,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and you can create materials with many different properties,"},{"time":250000,"text":"materials that are insulating, fire-resistant,"},{"time":253000,"text":"moisture-resistant, vapor-resistant --"},{"time":256000,"text":"materials that can absorb impacts, that can absorb acoustical impacts."},{"time":259000,"text":"But these materials are grown from agricultural byproducts,"},{"time":262000,"text":"not petroleum."},{"time":264000,"text":"And because they're made of natural materials,"},{"time":267000,"text":"they are 100 percent compostable"},{"time":269000,"text":"in you own backyard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"So I'd like to share with you the four basic steps"},{"time":274000,"text":"required to make these materials."},{"time":276000,"text":"The first is selecting a feedstock,"},{"time":278000,"text":"preferably something that's regional, that's in your area, right --"},{"time":280000,"text":"local manufacturing."},{"time":282000,"text":"The next is actually taking this feedstock and putting in a tool,"},{"time":285000,"text":"physically filling an enclosure, a mold,"},{"time":287000,"text":"in whatever shape you want to get."},{"time":289000,"text":"Then you actually grow the mycelium through these particles,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and that's where the magic happens,"},{"time":294000,"text":"because the organism is doing the work in this process,"},{"time":296000,"text":"not the equipment."},{"time":298000,"text":"The final step is, of course, the product,"},{"time":300000,"text":"whether it's a packaging material, a table top, or building block."},{"time":303000,"text":"Our vision is local manufacturing,"},{"time":305000,"text":"like the local food movement, for production."},{"time":307000,"text":"So we've created formulations for all around the world"},{"time":309000,"text":"using regional byproducts."},{"time":311000,"text":"If you're in China, you might use a rice husk"},{"time":314000,"text":"or a cottonseed hull."},{"time":316000,"text":"If you're in Northern Europe or North America,"},{"time":318000,"text":"you can use things like buckwheat husks or oat hulls."},{"time":322000,"text":"We then process these husks with some basic equipment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"And I want to share with you a quick video from our facility"},{"time":327000,"text":"that gives you a sense of how this looks at scale."},{"time":330000,"text":"So what you're seeing here is actually cotton hulls from Texas, in this case."},{"time":333000,"text":"It's a waste product."},{"time":335000,"text":"And what they're doing in our equipment"},{"time":337000,"text":"is going through a continuous system,"},{"time":339000,"text":"which cleans, cooks, cools"},{"time":342000,"text":"and pasteurizes these materials,"},{"time":344000,"text":"while also continuously inoculating them with our mycelium."},{"time":347000,"text":"This gives us a continuous stream of material"},{"time":349000,"text":"that we can put into almost any shape,"},{"time":351000,"text":"though today we're making corner blocks."},{"time":353000,"text":"And it's when this lid goes on the part,"},{"time":355000,"text":"that the magic really starts."},{"time":358000,"text":"Because the manufacturing process is our organism."},{"time":361000,"text":"It'll actually begin to digest these wastes"},{"time":363000,"text":"and, over the next five days,"},{"time":365000,"text":"assemble them into biocomposites."},{"time":368000,"text":"Our entire facility"},{"time":370000,"text":"is comprised of thousands and thousands and thousands of these tools"},{"time":373000,"text":"sitting indoors in the dark, quietly self-assembling materials --"},{"time":376000,"text":"and everything from building materials"},{"time":378000,"text":"to, in this case,"},{"time":380000,"text":"a packaging corner block."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"So I've said a number of times that we grow materials."},{"time":385000,"text":"And it's kind of hard to picture how that happens."},{"time":387000,"text":"So my team has taken five days-worth of growth,"},{"time":389000,"text":"a typical growth cycle for us,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and condensed it into a 15-second time lapse."},{"time":394000,"text":"And I want you to really watch closely"},{"time":396000,"text":"these little white dots on the screen,"},{"time":398000,"text":"because, over the five-day period,"},{"time":400000,"text":"what they do is extend out and through this material,"},{"time":403000,"text":"using the energy that's contained in these seed husks"},{"time":405000,"text":"to build this chitinous polymer matrix."},{"time":407000,"text":"This matrix self-assembles,"},{"time":409000,"text":"growing through and around the particles,"},{"time":411000,"text":"making millions and millions of tiny fibers."},{"time":414000,"text":"And what parts of the seed husk we don't digest,"},{"time":417000,"text":"actually become part of the final, physical composite."},{"time":420000,"text":"So in front of your eyes, this part just self-assembled."},{"time":422000,"text":"It actually takes a little longer. It takes five days."},{"time":425000,"text":"But it's much faster than conventional farming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"The last step, of course, is application."},{"time":430000,"text":"In this case, we've grown a corner block."},{"time":432000,"text":"A major Fortune 500 furniture maker"},{"time":435000,"text":"uses these corner blocks to protect their tables in shipment."},{"time":438000,"text":"They used to use a plastic packaging buffer,"},{"time":440000,"text":"but we were able to give them the exact same physical performance"},{"time":443000,"text":"with our grown material."},{"time":445000,"text":"Best of all, when it gets to the customer,"},{"time":448000,"text":"it's not trash."},{"time":450000,"text":"They can actually put this in their natural ecosystem without any processing,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and it's going to improve the local soil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"So, why mycelium?"},{"time":456000,"text":"The first reason is local open feedstocks."},{"time":458000,"text":"You want to be able to do this anywhere in the world"},{"time":460000,"text":"and not worry about peak rice hull or peak cottonseed hulls,"},{"time":462000,"text":"because you have multiple choices."},{"time":464000,"text":"The next is self-assembly,"},{"time":466000,"text":"because the organism is actually doing most of the work in this process."},{"time":469000,"text":"You don't need a lot of equipment to set up a production facility."},{"time":472000,"text":"So you can have lots of small facilities"},{"time":474000,"text":"spread all across the world."},{"time":476000,"text":"Biological yield is really important."},{"time":478000,"text":"And because 100 percent of what we put in the tool become the final product,"},{"time":481000,"text":"even the parts that aren't digested"},{"time":483000,"text":"become part of the structure,"},{"time":485000,"text":"we're getting incredible yield rates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"Natural polymers, well ... I think that's what's most important,"},{"time":490000,"text":"because these polymers have been tried and tested"},{"time":492000,"text":"in our ecosystem for the last billion years,"},{"time":494000,"text":"in everything from mushrooms to crustaceans."},{"time":497000,"text":"They're not going to clog up Earth's ecosystems. They work great."},{"time":500000,"text":"And while, today,"},{"time":502000,"text":"we can practically guarantee that yesterday's packaging"},{"time":504000,"text":"is going to be here in 10,000 years,"},{"time":506000,"text":"what I want to guarantee"},{"time":508000,"text":"is that in 10,000 years,"},{"time":510000,"text":"our descendants, our children's children,"},{"time":512000,"text":"will be living happily and in harmony"},{"time":515000,"text":"with a healthy Earth."},{"time":517000,"text":"And I think that can be some really good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}